tml#List.nil\">]</a><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">]</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.cyclicPermutations_nil","kind":"theorem","line":495,"name":"List.cyclicPermutations_nil","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.lean#L495-L497"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.cyclicPermutations\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">cyclicPermutations</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"List of all cyclic permutations of `l`.\nThe `cyclicPermutations` of a nonempty list `l` will always contain `List.length l` elements.\nThis implies that under certain conditions, there are duplicates in `List.cyclicPermutations l`.\nThe `n`th entry is equal to `l.rotate n`, proven in `List.get_cyclicPermutations`.\nThe proof that every cyclic permutant of `l` is in the list is `List.mem_cyclicPermutations_iff`.\n\n     cyclicPermutations [1, 2, 3, 2, 4] =\n       [[1, 2, 3, 2, 4], [2, 3, 2, 4, 1], [3, 2, 4, 1, 2],\n        [2, 4, 1, 2, 3], [4, 1, 2, 3, 2]] ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/List/Rotate.html#List.cyclicPermutations","kind":"def","line":482,"name":"List.cyclicPermutations","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7